1.title: Presidential Address
1.plot: As this new season begins, we take a recap of the last season, and what we have for this new season.

2.title: Caro Remix
2.plot: President Goodluck Ebele Jonathan and his political rival General Muhammadu Buhari do a remix on the hit Song Caro originally sang by Starboy Feat Wizkid. Get to hear these two political heavyweights as each one of them convinces voters to vote for them.

3.title: The Chicken Run of Lieberan
3.plot: In an attempt to run for the governor's seat, Labaran Maku resigns from Cabinet.

4.title: Fela Meets Wole
4.plot: The late Musician and human rights activist, Fela Kuti pays his cousin Wole Soyinka, The Nobel Peace Prize winner in Literature an unexpected visit, and they have discussion on the state of affairs of and politics of Nigeria.

5.title: Technomiles
5.plot: Enjoy the political hit Technomiles, with President Goodluck Jonathan.

6.title: APC Midweek Review Campaign
6.plot: Is John Dara's daughter Raza useful in the presidential elections? Find out here.

7.title: Austerity
7.plot: The Minister of State Finance, Ngozi, briefs president Goodluck Jonathan on the state of affairs.

8.title: Fergie Time
8.plot: Everything is poised for the February 14th elections...until someone decides an extension might be in his favor.

9.title: Arm Wrestling
9.plot: The fate of Nigeria hangs in the balance as the top presidential candidates engage in hand to hand combat for the top job.

10.title: Valentine's Day Blues
10.plot: It's different strokes for different political folks on Valentines day in the Buhari and Goodluck households.

11.title: Shekau's Shopping List
11.plot: The Boko Haram leader might be an outlaw, but in this video he discovers much to his distaste that Nigeria's problems are his problems too.

12.title: Six Weeks
12.plot: With the elections postponed, the military's top brass deliberate on performing magic in six weeks.

13.title: If I Were a Boy Remix
13.plot: Jonathan and Haribubu dabble in a bit of banter and wishful thinking as they remix Beyonce's hit song.

14.title: The Usual Suspects
14.plot: The police is your friend sometimes. Find out what happens when a couple report an armed robbery to the men in black.

15.title: Foreign Willy Willy in Lampedusa
15.plot: Our patriotic TV Host Mr. Foreign Willy Willy, scratches his head over the issue of African migrants seeking a better life in Europe and risking death in the process.

16.title: Obasanjo's Remix of 'Kas' 'Fimile'
16.plot: Obasanjo has broken his ties with the party he helped nurture for 16 years. In this remix of Kas' hit Fimile, Obasanjo tells the PDP to leave him alone.

17.title: The Military Conference
17.plot: Military Chiefs from the Lake Chad region discuss their latest offensive against the Boko boys.

18.title: GEJ and Haribubu at the AMVCAs
18.plot: GEJ and Haribubu are up for a prize at the prestigious Africa Magic Viewers' Choice Awards, but only one Oga will take the trophy home.

19.title: Haribubu in London
19.plot: Foreign Willy Willy investigates Haribubu's controversial visit to London.

20.title: Jona by Peshi P
20.plot: Dame Peshy searches for her dear Jona in this remix of Yemi Alade's hit song "Johnny".

21.title: Presidential Jet
21.plot: Jona laments to his aide and measures executive jets as Haribubu leaves him stranded on the tarmac.

22.title: Out with the Young
22.plot: Jona meets with Zuma and Mugabe, but can't seem to decide if young leaders are better than the old.

23.title: Mr. Nigeria Contest
23.plot: Cossy causes commotion as our leaders past and present strut their stuff for the title of Mr. Nigeria.

24.title: The Buhari School of Fitness Ad
24.plot: The austere General has some tips on staying fit physically and otherwise.

25.title: Tough Times Ahead
25.plot: The leading Presidential candidates get a glimpse into Nigeria's financial future courtesy Ngozi.

26.title: Shekau's Last Wish
26.plot: Besieged by the multinational forces, Shekau makes one last kinky request of his trusted lieutenant.

27.title: The Sooth Sayer Visit
27.plot: Tired of all the election anxiety, the GEJ and Peshy P. consult a soothsayer as a last resort. But what will the future throw their way?

28.title: The 911 by Jonathan and Peshi
28.plot: Shekau has vexed Peshy's husband! The President and First Lady threaten to deal with Shekau in this remix of Wyclef Jean and Mary J. Blige's 911

29.title: Pete Edochie for President
29.plot: The perennial Igwe of Nollywood shocks everyone by throwing his red cap into the race for President. With support from his Nollywood friends

30.title: Asari Dokubo Press Conference
30.plot: The loud mouthed Mujahid spits a little fire and a lot of hot air in support of GEJ's second term, but can he stand and make good his threats?

31.title: Ole de Thief
31.plot: In this remix of D'Banj's worldwide hit Oliver Twist, Nigerians take shots at thiefy-thiefy pen-robber politicians.

32.title: Fela for President
32.plot: Worried by soaring prices of essential commodities, the Abami Eda decides to make yet another bid for the highest office in the land.

33.title: Home and Abroad
33.plot: Foreign Willy Willy tries to find out what Diasporan and home based Nigerians think of one another.

34.title: Pastor Ayo's Pre-Election Prayer
34.plot: GEJ's favorite flamboyant pastor offers a prayer for the elections by remixing Chris Brown's "Loyal".

35.title: The Detention of Pawpaw
35.plot: Aki comes to rescue of his good friend PawPaw from the police and some Nollywood abracadabra ensues.

36.title: My Favorite Nollywood Things
36.plot: Cossy reminds us of some of the things that make Nigeria movies so special to us all.

37.title: Haribubu's Victory Speech
37.plot: Haribubu delivers a speech on his historic victory, but will he stick to the script?

38.title: Concession Call
38.plot: After the just completed general elections, former president Goodluck Jonathan, calls General Buhari, to congratulate him on his victory.

39.title: Presidential Villa
39.plot: Patience gets mad on seeing a beautiful lady in her husband's office.

40.title: Mama Pissed
40.plot: After the fifth quadrennial election to be held since the end of military rule in Nigeria, first lady Patience Jonathan gets very annoyed after the Incumbent President Goodluck Ebele Jonathan conceded defeat, in the most expensive election ever to be held on the African continent.

41.title: Boko Salaam
41.plot: With the stern General Haribubu on his way into office, Shekau The Shameless reconsiders his options.

42.title: Busted Buhari
42.plot: Haribubu indulges in the sort of nostalgia that gives Tinubu sleepless nights.

43.title: The Lie Detector
43.plot: In a quest to determine the fate of the kidnapped girls, Jonathan subjects the Boko Haram leader to a newly purchased lie detector machine.

44.title: Jonathan Amanpour
44.plot: President Goodluck Jonathan is on the hot seat and is interviewed by an American interviewer on Amanpour.

45.title: Good Cop, Bad Cop
45.plot: Captain Azokwo of the Nigerian Police experiences first hand harassment by police officers in a bid go extort some money from him as a bribe.

46.title: Bayelsa
46.plot: Aso Villa to Otouke? There is no shame in President Jonathan's relocation game as we discover in this remix of Akon's breakthrough hit "Ghetto".

47.title: Free Readers Association of Nigeria
47.plot: Foreign Willy Willy visits the famous freeloading philosophers at the newspaper vendor's stand.

48.title: Certified General
48.plot: Haribubu's certificate scandal looks like it will never end. Or will it?

49.title: Be Social
49.plot: With technology making the world a global village, it is easy to communicate to the whole world in a matter of seconds. But is this new invented hobby very safe? Is one's security assured by this new technology? Nigerians have a growing penchant for selfies and social media shakara. But what happens when it all goes too far?

50.title: I'm Coming Home
50.plot: After losing the national elections to General Muhammadu Buhari, the incumbent president Goodluck Jonathan tugs belatedly at our heartstrings in this almost emotional remix of the Diddy Dirty Money hit I am coming home. Listen to this beautiful hit as he expresses his feelings, despair and anxiety of loosing his presidential seat.

51.title: Abacha's Request
51.plot: The goggled ghostly general makes a surprising demand of the country he allegedly looted.

52.title: The Defecto App
52.plot: Finally, an app that makes things easy for turncoat politicians.

53.title: Change Is Here?
53.plot: What do Mugabe, Obama, Fela, and Kongi think about Nigeria's freshly acquired Change? Foreign Willy Willy finds out.

1.title: LETTERS, LETTERS and MORE LETTERS
1.plot: President Goodluck Jonathan finds himself buried under a pile of letters, and Patience is running out of patience.

2.title: JONATHAN UNDECIDED
2.plot: President Goodluck Jonathan 'undecides' to run for re-election in 2015 in his interview with Christiane Amanpour... #JonathanUndecided

3.title: PRESIDENT JONATHAN and SANUSI
3.plot: President Jonathan and (former) Central Bank Governor Sanusi spend a night at the casino and make a $20 billion bet....

4.title: THE CENTENARY CELEBRATION
4.plot: Naija celebrates its Centenary with a fresh take on Kool &; The Gang's famous song! Let's celebrate our oil tonight, come on!

5.title: Abacha's Interview
5.plot: General Sani Abacha comes back from Hell for this exclusive interview.

6.title: OBASANJO's BIRTHDAY
6.plot: Former president Obasanjo celebrates his birthday and receives a card from Goodluck Jonathan...

7.title: THE NATIONAL CONFERENCE
7.plot: A receptionist fails to recognize General Abacha at a National Conference, Is the legacy being forgotten?

8.title: NO HONOUR AMONG THIEVES
8.plot: When a member of a gang of thieves forgets to bribe the police; drama ensues

9.title: THE WENDELL SIMLIN SCANDAL
9.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

10.title: GOODLUCK'S JET
10.plot: Goodluck Jonathan is stuck at an airport as his jet breaks down. But where are the 9 other jets allocated to him?

11.title: TINUBU WASHINGTON DC INTERVIEW
11.plot: Opposition leader Bola Tinobu is interviewed while on a trip to DC to visit his dentist. He talks about the wealth he accumulated as governor and his tactic to win next year's election.

12.title: BUHARI and TINUBU HEART to HEART
12.plot: Muhammadu Buhari and Bola Tinubu discuss their days in the army and their political future.

13.title: Tinubu, Buhari and Jonathan Talk Politics
13.plot: President Jonathan, Bola Tinubu and Muhammadu Buhari have a late night talk on the Aso Villa grounds about Nigerian politics, friends and enemies.

14.title: Nigerian Ministry of Information: Boko Haram and the Abuja Jailbreak
14.plot: The Nigerian Ministry of Information holds a press conference to announce successes in the fight against Boko Haram and discuss details of the attempted Abuja jailbreak.

15.title: Jonathan and Zuma Debate Who Has the Biggest... Economy
15.plot: Goodluck Jonathan and South African President Jacob Zuma debate the rebasing of the Nigerian economy.

16.title: The National Conference: Kola Nuts and Daily Nap
16.plot: Our correspondent reports from the National Conference where delegates are more concerned about kola nuts and their daily nap than the future of Nigeria.

17.title: Drunk in Power by G.E.J. and Dame Patience
17.plot: The high-flying duo of G.E.J (Goodluck Jonathan) and Dame Patience sing 'Drunk with Power', a remix of Beyonce and Jay-Z's hit 'Drunk in love'. In this hit, the first couple detail their love for each other as well as their aspirations for 2015. Dame Patience sings of "sleeping on the ground floor and walking up upstairs and wondering what the hell happened" , in depiction of Jonathan's meteoric rise to the eventual tenancy of Aso Rock, beating everybody else's expectations.

18.title: Tinubu "Rack City" remix
18.plot: King Tinubu performs a spirited remix of Tyga's "Rack City"! Racking up the money: he knows it best.

19.title: Tinubu and Buhari, APC the Wedding Planners
19.plot: After the media circus around the wedding of Jonathan's daughter, Tinubu and Buhari decide to plan a wedding of their own: the bride, the groom, and oh yes... the iPhones.

20.title: The Nigerian Economy, Rebased
20.plot: In our new segment "What are they saying?", we take to the streets to find out what regular Nigerians think about Nigeria now being the biggest economy in Africa.

21.title: Jonathan Praises Di Papa
21.plot: President Jonathan stands with Pastor Oritsejafor in "Praising Di Papa" for his daughter's luxurious wedding, and the many other things he is thankful for.

22.title: Jonathan Is Running Again... On His Big Feet
22.plot: President Jonathan meets an enthusiastic voter over dinner and finally declares how and why he wants to run again.

23.title: G.E.J.'s "Gold Caller" remix
23.plot: G.E.J. performs "Gold Caller", a remix of Kanye West's "Gold Digger", in which he denies actually being a gold caller but admits that he is no broke caller.

24.title: All They Do Is Steal Remix
24.plot: The Ogas remix DJ Khaled's hit song "All They Do is Win" into "All They Do is Steal". Stealing is their mission!

25.title: Who Wants to Be the President's Daughter?
25.plot: Beauties from across Nigeria battle it out for a chance to win the president's second name in preparation for the next gold-plated wedding.

26.title: The Recurrent Expenditure
26.plot: From items to stimulate the forthcoming elections to Dame's shopping list, a good budget needs to plan for it all.

27.title: Happy: Ogas at the Top Version
27.plot: Our Ogas at the Top take over Pharell Williams' hit song!

28.title: The Diplomatic Chat
28.plot: The art of Not answering questions as perfected by G.E.J.

29.title: The End of the Affair
29.plot: APC luminaries General Buhari and Chief Tinubu disagree on how best to...sweep Nigeria

30.title: Personally by G.E.J and Dame Patience
30.plot: In this spoof of P square's " Personally", G.E.J promises to square it out with the enemies of his regime.

32.title: Anywhere But Chibok
32.plot: GEJ heads to Paris from where he makes a statement on Chibok.

33.title: Man Alone
33.plot: Jonathan leaves Dame behind to embark on a delicate search for the girls.

34.title: #Bingbackourgirlsforthesakeof2015
34.plot: After Patience's "There is God-Oh", Jonathan puts his own appeal on video.

35.title: Corruption Is Not Theft
35.plot: Now see how you can quickly spot the difference and take it to court...

36.title: Help Outsourced
36.plot: President Goodluck activates his international networks in the search for the missing girls.

37.title: Shut Up and Fly, Feat. DAM (Diezani Alison-Madueke)
37.plot: In this spoof Hit of Rihanna's Shut Up and Drive, Lady DAM launches a recruitment for the most qualified pilot to fly her fine-tuned, supersonic Gulfstream jet.

38.title: Umbrella by PDP
38.plot: Forget Rihanna's Umbrella, these PDP artists will dazzle you as they make it rain under G.E.J's umbrella

39.title: The Boko Haram "Scoop"
39.plot: Watch as this foreign correspondent makes history with this spectacular Boko Haram story.

40.title: Imagine by Jonathan
40.plot: Here is Aso rock's perfect rendition of Imagine by John Lenon where G.E.J shows us how to get it all done by just capturing it in the mind

41.title: Drop It Like It's Hot by APC
41.plot: A Single by APC rapper General Buhari aka Haribubu featuring The Jagaban from the album B&B (Buhari & Bola) : The Gangsta Collabo. The first to be produced under their Broom records and inspired by Snoop Dogg's Drop It Like It's Hot Ft. Pharell Williams.

42.title: Match Fixing
42.plot: Our reporter goes to the streets to have the ordinary citizens weigh in on the super eagles match fixing scandal and every other thing being fixed in the country.

43.title: National Security Priority
43.plot: Finally, President Goodluck gives the armed forces the mandate to wipe out the Number one threat to national security.... the BringBackOurGirls protesters!

44.title: The Madueke Massage
44.plot: Join Lady Alison as she unwinds after a long, hard and oily day.

45.title: The APC Conference
45.plot: Watch as Bola and the General discuss the state of affairs within their party and how best to sweep towards 2015

46.title: Jonathan, Shekau and the Lie Detector
46.plot: Unhappy with the state of insecurity in the country, the president summons the Boko Haram leader and subjects him to a lie Detector. Then this happens...

47.title: Peshy Skypes Wole Soyinka!
47.plot: If you have never heard a real Port Harcourt girl call up a Nobel Laureate to warn him about his "useless, stupid,yeye mouth", then this should be the clip for you!

48.title: Anything for Vote
48.plot: General Buhari aka Haribubu on a charm offensive, fashioning himself as the youth friendly option for 2015. He gets some things about the youth but some...well, he just doesn't

49.title: State of the Nation with Patrick Obahiagbon
49.plot: Hon Obahiagbon talks about " the series of unjustifiable higi-hagas and maniacal crincum-crancums which have manufactured a state of anomie that endangers the autochthonous proliferation of malfeasance within the geometrical coordinates of our cataclysmic Naija space!"
